data.enText: a page or series of pages showing the days, weeks and months of a particular year, especially one that you hang on a wall
a record of what you have to do each day; the book in which you write this down

data.chText: （一年之中的）重大事件（或重要日期）一览表
data.enText: a list of important events or dates of a particular type during the year

data.chText: 这是全年赛马日程表中最重要的几个星期之一。
data.enText: This is one of the biggest weeks in the racing calendar.
a system by which time is divided into fixed periods, showing the beginning and end of a year

word_means: 把…记入日程表中；把…列入表中；为作分类索引
simple_means.memory_skill: calend 每月第一天 + ar 表物 → 日历

means: (一年之中的)重大事件(或重要日期)一览表
把…记入日程表中；把…列入表中；为(文件等)作分类索引

ex.chText: 他安排了一个紧凑的旅行日程。
ex.enText: He has planned a tight travel schedule.

ex.chText: 你已经安排了考试日程吗?
ex.enText: Have you made the examination schedule?
The project was completed ahead of schedule.

synonyms.bx: 指做某事的计划及具体运作的时间表。

ex.chText: 我们必须将这件事提上议事日程。
ex.enText: We must put this item on the agenda.

ex.chText: 会议主席说今天下午有一长串待议事项。
ex.enText: The chairman says there is a lengthy agenda this afternoon.

synonyms.bx: 主要指会议上需要商议解决的问题的一览表。

ex.chText: 他的个人日程表上记着5月5日有个约会。
ex.enText: There is a notation about an appointment on his personal calendar for May 5.

ex.chText: 依照大学的日程表，你们的考试将在7月举行。
ex.enText: According to the university calendar your examinations will be in July.

ex.chText: 总统选举是明年政治日程表上的大事。
ex.enText: The presidential election is the highlight of next year's political calendar.

synonyms.bx: 指某人在记事簿上记下的要做各项事情的计划，也指某个团体或某项活动一年内重大事件的日程安排。

ex.chText: 第一份航空时刻表是在1928年由泛美航空公司刊印的。
ex.enText: The first airplane timetable was published by Pan-American Airways in 1928.

ex.chText: 我这星期的时间安排很紧。
ex.enText: I've got a very busy timetable this week.

ex.chText: 大雾打乱了他们的旅行日程。
ex.enText: The heavy fog upset their timetable for the trip.

synonyms.bx: 比 schedule 更为具体，常指车、船、航班等的时刻表，也指课程表或活动计划的时间表。

synonym.guide: 导航词义：时间表，计划表

tr: a list or register of events (appointments or social events or court cases etc)
example: I have you on my calendar for next Monday

tr: a tabular array of the days (usually for one year)
a system of timekeeping that defines the beginning and length and divisions of the year

value.def: A calendar is a chart or device which displays the date and the day of the week, and often the whole of a particular year divided up into months, weeks, and days.

example.ex: There was a calendar on the wall above, with large squares around the dates.
example.tran: 上面的墙上挂着日历,日期上画着大大的方框。

value.def: A calendar is a particular system for dividing time into periods such as years, months, and weeks, often starting from a particular point in history.

example.ex: The Christian calendar was originally based on the Julian calendar of the Romans.
example.tran: 公历最初是以罗马人的儒略历为基础制定的。

value.def: You can use calendar to refer to a series or list of events and activities which take place on particular dates, and which are important for a particular organization, community, or person.

example.ex: It is one of the British sporting calendar's most prestigious events...
example.tran: 这是英国体坛大事表上最负盛名的赛事之一。

example.ex: Franklin joined her and the children whenever his crowded calendar allowed...
example.tran: 只要能从百忙之中抽出空,富兰克林就会陪在妻儿身边。

example.ex: They tried to make a calendar of Spain's festivals.
example.tran: 他们打算做个西班牙节日活动一览表。

value.tran: (某一组织、团体或个人的)日程表，纪事表，大事一览表

trans: 基督降临历(儿童每天打开一扇编了号的小门，里面有图片或巧克力)
公历，阳历，格列高利历(自1582年以来西方国家使用的历法)
儒略历(凯撒大帝制订的日历，在西方国家一直使用至以阳历取代为止)
日历月(一年十二个月中的一个月)
日历年(公历1月1日至12月31日)
